Clip

library(raster)
library(rgeos)
## rgeos version: 0.3-21, (SVN revision 540)
##  GEOS runtime version: 3.4.2-CAPI-1.8.2 r3921 
##  Linking to sp version: 1.2-3 
##  Polygon checking: TRUE
gClip <- function(shp, bb) {
  if(class(bb) == "matrix") b_poly <- as(extent(as.vector(t(bb))), "SpatialPolygons") 
  else b_poly <- as(extent(bb), "SpatialPolygons")
  gIntersection(shp, b_poly, byid = T)
}


xs <- c(-76.47916, -75.90119)
ys <- c(42.78893, 43.22481)

b <- bbox(syr)
b[1, ] <- xs
b[2, ] <- ys

syr_clipped <- gClip(syr, b)
## Warning in RGEOSBinTopoFunc(spgeom1, spgeom2, byid, id, drop_lower_td,
## unaryUnion_if_byid_false, : spgeom1 and spgeom2 have different proj4
## strings
roads_clipped <- gClip(roads, b)
## Warning in RGEOSBinTopoFunc(spgeom1, spgeom2, byid, id, drop_lower_td,
## unaryUnion_if_byid_false, : spgeom1 and spgeom2 have different proj4
## strings
interstate_clipped <- gClip(interstate, b)
## Warning in RGEOSBinTopoFunc(spgeom1, spgeom2, byid, id, drop_lower_td,
## unaryUnion_if_byid_false, : spgeom1 and spgeom2 have different proj4

Plot Clipped

plot( syr_clipped,  border="gray80" )
